  						<table border='0' cellpadding='3' cellspacing='0' width='92%'>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' align='center'>CHAPTER 5: LIELAY'S ADVENTURES</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><font face='verdana' size='2pt'><p>"Let's get going! We're burning daylight!"</p>

   <p>Albain was in front of the group leading them to where Lielay was last seen. All the elves were in armor and each wielded a weapon for protection.</p>

     <p>"She was last seen here," Albain stood on the spot where Lielay fell, "now split up in groups of three and start looking."</p>

   <p>Albain, Joshua, and another elf named Sawn Shroomfoot set off down a path by the orc camp.</p>

   <p>An orc came down the stairs and stopped in front of Lielay and Danny's cell. Lielay was asleep and Danny was leaning on the wall, he glared at the orc.</p> 

     <p>"What do you want." Danny sneered at the orc.</p>

   <p>The orc pointed to Lielay. Then behind it the huge orc came with the wood elf translator. The orc started to talk to the elf fast. After a few minutes the elf spoke.</p>

     <p>"Lord Vic'Nance would like to have her come back up now. Wake her up.... now."</p>

   <p>Danny just stared.</p> 

     <p>"Now, elf, or else Rocky," the huge orc puffed up, "will come in there."</p>

     <p>"All right, all right. Hold on." Danny didn't want that thing to come in.</p>

   <p>He walked over to where Lielay slept and gently shook her awake. She stirred and sat up. She opened her eyes and saw the orcs.</p> 

     <p>"What is tat thing doing here." she pointed to the orc.</p> 

     <p>"Lielay. The Lord wants you up there." Danny choked.</p> 

   <p>The cell door opened and the smaller orc came in and walked over to Lielay. Danny was pushed aside and Lielay was grabbed by the wrist again. She was pulled out of the cell and up the stairs. The cell door shut and locked. Danny was alone again.</p>

   <p>Lielay was led back up the stairs and through the doors and back into the throne room. Lord Vic'Nance was still sitting on his throne. He smiled when Lielay entered. He clapped his hands together and another servant brought a tray with two goblets and a bowl of figs on it.</p>

    <p> "Step up here Lielay Liltreehuggr." Lord Vic'Nance said and waved her up. </p>

   <p>Lielay walked up to the throne and stood in front of the lord. He motioned Lielay to sit in the chair next to him. It wasn't as comfy as the throne but Lielay didn't complain.</p> 

  <p> Albain, Joshua, and Sawn were walking in the direction of Lord Vic'Nance's fort, slowly. They looked in bushes, behind trees, and rocks for any sign of Lielay. They haven't run into any orcs.... yet.</p>

    <p> “I’m tired of walking in all this armor. Shouldn’t we have found a sign by now?” Sawn sat on the ground and removed his helmet.</p> 

     <p>“We don’t have time to rest. We haven’t found any sign of Lielay because they haven’t killed her; she’s still alive. I can feel it.” Joshua was turning into another Albain.</p> 

    <p> “Just what I would say.” Albain showed a weak smile.</p> 

  <p> Sawn sighed and stood up. He picked up his helmet and started walking with the other two. Not to far ahead and to the left was Lord Vic’Nance’s fort.</p> 

   <p>Back in the fort where Lielay was, Lord Vic’Nance was trying to start conversation with her, but all she did was sigh and turn her head.</p> 

   <p>  “Lielay. Your quarters shall be below mine, you shall become my maid. Whenever I call for you, you shall come.”</p>

  <p> Lielay sighed and looked at the wall aimlessly. </p>

    <p> “Are you even listening to me? Maybe you should go back down into that cell of yours for some more time.”</p>

   <p>Lielay jumped at the sound of her going back into that cell. Lord Vic’Nance saw this and laughed.</p> 

    <p> “So you want to go back. Who is in that cell with you? Answer me!”</p>

  <p> She said nothing. The translator elf stepped forward and bowed.</p> 

     <p>“M’lord, a male prisoner shared the same cell with her. His name is,” he peered at a scroll, “Danny Oakfeller. Somehow those two know eachother.”</p>

   <p>He stepped back and the lord turned to Lielay and smiled. He rubbed his hands together evilly.</p> 

     <p>“We won’t be sending you down there anymore.” He smiled. </p>

    <p> “What! Why not!” Lielay blurted out. </p>
    
     <p> “Oh, so you do know him. How?”</p>

    <p> “He…. I…. We….”</p>

     <p>“If you don’t answer me I’ll have him executed!”</p>

     <p>“OK, OK! I’ll tell, Danny Oakfeller is my….my husband.”</p>

     <p>“Oh, how interesting. Now I know not to send you down there anymore.”</p>

  <p> Lielay fell back into the chair and held in her tears. She was praying to Tunare that she would protect Danny, Albain, Caleb, and Joshua.</p>

  <p>“Rocky, take her to her quarters.” Lord Vic’Nance said lazily.</p>

   <p>Rocky grabbed Lielay and pulled her through the doors again. Instead of going down stairs he led her up stairs. Lielay’s quarters where to the right on the second to top floor. Rocky opened the door and pushed her inside, he then slammed the door shut and locked it. Lielay heard him walk away.</p> 

    <p> “Damn it!’ she cursed out loud. </p>

<p>   Albain, Joshua, and Sawn were cornered in by five orcs. The orcs smiled because they thought that they had won the battle. Albain smiled too, he looked at every orc then looked at Joshua and Sawn and winked. </p>

   <p>Albain raised his hand, pretending to yawn, then mana started gaining in his palm.  The orcs stared in awe. The spell shot out of his hand and hit the orcs full blast. They all were enveloped in flames and fell to the ground screaming in agony. </p>

<p>   Joshua ran forward and sliced one orc’s head off, he was burned by the flames. Sawn extended his sword and cut off another two orc head’s, he wasn’t burned. There was two left, still burning. They howled in pain, loudly. To loud. The three wood elves heard a sound like a small stampede. </p>

     <p>“What’s that?” Sawn asked as he looked around. </p>

   <p>  “I have no idea.” Joshua said as he looked too. </p>

   <p>They looked forward and saw a large group of orcs running towards them. The three were still blocked in, plus if they ran they wouldn’t have gotten very far because of their armor. They braced themselves for the blow of the orcs.</p>

  <p> The orcs surrounded the three and were closing in. The three dropped to their weapons and began to pray to Tunare.  The orcs stopped and saw them praying, they ran up to the elves and grabbed hem. Each elf was being led and captured by four orcs each. </p>

  <p> Still in his cell, Danny paced back and forth thinking of a plan to escape the prison and save Lielay. The prisoner in the cell across from Danny’s watched him with interest. Danny saw him staring at him. </p>

   <p>  “What!” Danny barked at him. </p>

   <p>  “Nothing, just think it’s funny you get something you want and then you lose it right away.”</p>

   <p>Danny was confused at first about what he said but then he figured it out, Lielay.</p>

  <p> Lielay was pounding on the door, shouting and cursing for them to let her out. She went to the window on the other side of the room and looked down. She let out a scream when she saw how far up she was. There would be no way down unless she wanted to risk her life by climbing down by windowsills.</p>

 <p> The orcs led Albain, Joshua, and Sawn through the gates of the fortress and through the big front doors. Their armor clanked along as hey were pushed into rooms. Finally they entered the throne room, Lord Vic’Nance was still sitting on his throne. </p>

    <p>“Now what do you want.” The lord said to the orcs.</p>

    <p> “More prisoners.” The translator spoke.</p> 

     <p>“More. We just got one a couple of hours ago. If they are all males throw them in some cells down in the dungeon.”</p> 

   <p>Joshua, Albain, and Sawn at first tried to struggle but there were to many orcs around them. They were pushed down the same stairs Lielay was pushed down a couple hours before them. They entered the prison and one orc opened the cell from across Danny’s and threw Sawn in there. Danny’s cell opened and Albain and Joshua were shoved in there. </p>

  <p> The orcs left and Joshua looked over across at Sawn. Albain’s eyes were on Danny. He poked Joshua and Joshua too turned around and stared.</p> 

     <p>“What are you staring at.” Danny said coldly. </p>

    <p> “I guess our new cell-mate.” Joshua said semi-cheery.</p> 

     <p>“Hey! I’m still over here!” Sawn shouted. </p>

    <p>“Your fine so shutup.” Albain yelled back. </p>

     <p>“Fine then.”</p>

  <p> Sawn turned around and started conversation with he elf in the cell with him. </p>

    <p>“Hey there are only two beds in this cell. God damn it, if I’m going to stay in here I get my own bed!” Albain pointed out.</p>

 <p> Rocky and another orc came down the stairs again and looked into the cells. Rocky too noticed that there were three in a cell instead of two. He opened the door and grabbed to Joshua who was the closest. Joshua was pushed into the cell next to Sawn’s. </p>

     <p>“Great now I’m stuck in a cell with this guy.” Albain told Sawn. </p>

   <p>Danny grabbed Albain and flung his around. He glared into Albain’s eyes like there were fire in them. </p>

    <p> “If you gotta problem with me, tell it to me not to your buddies. I don’t tolerate anything. I’ve been stuck in this cell for five years!”</p>

 <p>  Danny threw Albain to the floor and stocked off towards his bed. He sat down and Albain stood up. Albain glared at Danny and started to take off his heavy armor. He was now in his regular clothes. </p>

     <p>“Well who are you so I can at least call you by your name.” Albain asked. </p>

   <p>  “It’s Danny. Yours?” Danny replied. </p>

    <p> “The Great Albain Tinderblade. May I ask of your last name too?” Albain raised an eyebrow. </p>

   <p> “If you must. Danny Oakfeller.” </p>

  <p> Oakfeller. It knocked Albain flat on the ground again. This was Lielay’s husband, which means Lielay was still legally married and she was committed to another man. Albain couldn’t breath. Joshua tried to see what was happening but only saw Albain on the ground. </p>

    <p> “Albain what happened?” Joshua said through the bars of his cell.</p> 

    <p> “This….. this is Danny Oakfeller!”</p> 

    <p> “What! You mean the Oakfeller Lie was married too!?”</p>

     <p>“How do you know my wife?”</p>
     
<p>“How do I know her. I’m her brother. Joshua Liltreehuggr. Remember me?” Joshua tried to make himself visible.</p>

     <p>“What about you Tinderblade?”</p>

     <p>“I know her from me saving her life some times. I explore with her.”</p>

    <p>“You what, for how long!?”</p>

    <p> “For more then a week by now.” Albain pondered. </p>

  <p> Back up in her room Lielay was now throwing chairs and other objects around the room. She was one pissed off wood elf. Then it hit her. The perfect idea. She had just leaned the spell, snare, from Albain and she could use it the next time someone came into the room. </p>

    <p> “Perfect!” Lielay shouted. </p>

  <p> She sat down calmly on the bed and then waited for someone to come. She sat for ten minutes and decided to make a huge noise that would reach someone’s ears. She started throwing vases and other breakable things out the window and on the floor.</p> 

    <p> “Now I have to wait again.”</p>

   <p>This time someone did come. An orc from outside opened the door and stared at the mess Lielay had made. He looked at Lie and frowned, she smirked. Out of no where a spell shot out from her hand and the orc had roots climbing up it’s body. Lielay ran over and took the sword from the orc and killed it. </p>

   <p>   “Pathetic fool.” Lielay muttered and ran out the room. </p>

 <p>  Since the time Albain, Joshua, Sawn, and Danny were talking last they began to hatch a plan for their escape. They had one idea about jumping the orc that holds the keys, they talked about other ideas, but jumping the orc was the best plan. </p>

     <p>“Next time it comes down here, we’ll do it.” Danny said to everyone in the prison.</p> 

   <p>Lielay was careful about turning down corridors, watching for any orcs or elves. She still held the bloody sword in her hands. She already made it down two flights of stairs and saw nothing and no one. </p>

   <p> “So far so good.” She whispered. </p>

   <p>She looked down the stairs and saw nothing. Se ran down them and stopped at the corner. Looking around se saw a small orc fumbling wit his belt. It seemed to be falling off, it walked and tried to fix its belt at the same time. </p>
     
<p>“Yoo-hoo.” Lielay called.</p>

  <p>The orc looked up and saw nothing in view. It started to walk in Lielay’s direction, it pasted where she stood. Lielay went behind it and stabbed it in the back till it died. </p>

    <p>Lielay raced down the next flight of stairs and she wasn’t looking when she ran into the orc that held the keys to the prison. The orc drew its sword and challenged Lie to a duel. </p>

    <p> “OK, but your gonna lose.” Lielay sighed and held her sword up. </p>

   <p>The orc jabbed the sword towards her, it didn’t know how to fight. Lielay laughed and sliced the orc’s leg. It held its leg and started to back away from hr. Lielay felt sorry for it so she made its death swift and painless. </p>

    <p> “Thanks for the keys.” Lielay said as she took them. </p>

   <p>Down one last flight of stairs she went into the prison. She heard a voice then everything was silent. She moved slowly to the cells. Her sword was still up, covered with blood. </p>

    <p> “Now!” came a voice from the cell to her left. </p>

 <p>  Four arms shot out and grabbed hr. She was pulled into the cell with such force that it knocked her out. The sword fell loudly to the floor. </p>

    <p>“We got it!” Joshua said happily. </p>

    <p> “No we didn’t. We got Lie.” Albain said horrified.</p> 

   <p>Everyone then stared at the body crumbled in front of the cell. Albain and Danny’s eyes were wide open, frozen with horror. Joshua was at his cell door, so was Sawn and the other elf. </p>

    <p> “So that’s the druid we’re supposed to rescue.” Sawn’s voice broke the silence. </p> 

    <p> “Is…is….did we kill her?” Danny’s voice said shakily.</p> 

  <p>Albain got the keys and opened the cell door. He ran over and freed all the other elves. Danny was kneeling down beside Lielay. Joshua hovered over her too. Sawn was at the stairs watching for anything. Albain rushed over to Lielay’s side. </p>

   <p> “Lie, Lie?” Are you dead?” Albain remembered the sarnak. He was waiting for her reply. Nothing.</p>

    <p> “Is he was dead how would she answer?” Danny snapped. </p>
    
<p> “It’s an inside joke.” Albain snapped back. </p>

  <p> Danny started shaking Lielay and asked Joshua to lightly shake her head back and forth. After a minute Lielay’s eyelids fluttered. Her eyes opened and she was staring up at both Danny and Albain. </p>

     <p>“Lie you are alive!” Albain said almost about to cry.</p>

    <p>“I thought I lost you there, green eyes.” Danny said.</p> 

    <p> “You two jumped me. How could you? I cant believe you.” She smiled, joking.</p> 

   <p>Danny hugged her and finally let go. She stood up and turned to everyone in the room. </p>

    <p> “Having a party, are we?”</p>

     <p>“Sorta.” Joshua said behind her. </p>

  <p> Albain embraced Lielay and kissed her on the cheek. Danny steamed when Albain did that. He pulled Lielay away from him. Joshua then came over and hugged her, Danny let them since they were brother and sister. </p>

     <p>“Enough of that. We gotta get out of here before those orcs come back.” Sawn said and headed up the stairs. </p>
 </font></td>
	</tr>
